HEADWORD: Anubis
<hw>A*nu"bis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>An Egyptian deity, the conductor of departed
spirits to judgment, represented by a human figure with the head of a
jackal, dog or fox.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anunnaki</ent>⟦br⟧
